          <h2>Physical Characteristics</h2>
          <p>Mars is a terrestrial planet with a thin atmosphere and a solid, rocky surface marked by impact craters, valleys, deserts, and polar ice caps. Though often compared to Earth, Mars is considerably smaller and less massive, which has profoundly affected its geological and atmospheric evolution.</p>

          <div class="info-box glass">
